title: HEALTHCARE ANALYTICS: FROM DATA TO KNOWLEDGE TO HEALTHCARE IMPRO
description: Author: Hui Yang, Eva K. Lee Edition: 1 edition Publication Date: August 1, 2016 Publisher: Wiley ISBN-10: 1118919394 ISBN-13: 978-1118919392 Pages: 632 pages Format: pdf Size: 6.5M --- With a focus on cutting-edge approaches to the quickly growing field of healthcare, Healthcare Analytics: From Data to Knowledge to Healthcare Improvement provides an integrated and comprehensive treatment on recent research advancements in data-driven healthcare analytics in an effort to provide more personalized and smarter healthcare services. Emphasizing data and healthcare analytics from an operational management and statistical perspective, the book details how analytical methods and tools can be utilized to enhance healthcare quality and operational efficiency. --- http://dlfeb.com/book/healthcare-analytics-from-data-to-knowledge-to-healthcare-improvement-wiley-series-in-operations-research-and-management-science/
